# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# data/
#
# This directory is the read-only source of truth (Phase 0) and is NOT excluded
# wholesale: the small curated CSVs are what make `POST /ingestion/load` work on
# a fresh clone, and a repository whose demo cannot run is not a demo. What is
# excluded below is excluded for a stated reason, not for convenience.
#
# NOTE: an ignore rule only affects UNTRACKED files. These paths were staged
# before this section existed, so they also had to be removed from the index
# with `git rm --cached` (which leaves them untouched on disk -- data/ is never
# modified).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# The two Tier-1 datasets that are LOOKUP_ONLY by design (ADR/registry): they
# are streamed live by providers and deliberately have no loader, which is why
# SQLite stays ~18 MB against 1.6 GB of source data. They are also both over
# GitHub's hard 100 MB limit, so this is not a preference -- the push is
# rejected outright with them present.
#   SAML-D.csv                 950 MB / 9.5M rows
#   opensanctions_targets.csv  466 MB / 1.3M rows
# Without them the app degrades honestly (the providers report their status
# rather than inventing results), which is the behaviour those providers exist
# to demonstrate. See docs/datasets.md to obtain them.
data/aml_transactions/SAML-D.csv
data/sanctions/opensanctions_targets.csv

# ~190 MB of a leftover privacy/GDPR project that shares this folder by
# accident. It is never registered as a KYC source and no code path reads it,
# so shipping it would just be freight. Ignored here, kept on disk.
data/opp115/
data/privacy_qa/
data/gdpr_text/
data/gdpr.json
data/gdpr_articles.csv
data/gcapi.dll
